title: An in-range update of source-map-support is breaking the build üö®
body:
## The devDependency [source-map-support](https://github.com/evanw/node-source-map-support) was updated from `0.5.10` to `0.5.11`. üö® [View failing branch](https://github.com/0xProject/0x-monorepo/compare/development...0xProject:greenkeeper%2Fsource-map-support-0.5.11). This version is **covered** by your **current version range** and after updating it in your project **the build failed**. source-map-support is a devDependency of this project. It **might not break your production code or affect downstream projects**, but probably breaks your build or test tools, which may **prevent deploying or publishing**.
